## 🔶 What Needs Finishing — Prioritized

### Priority 1: Connect Autonomous Agents to LLM Reasoning

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is the **single most impactful remaining work**. The autonomous loop has the structure (goals, steps, budget, AAB ledger) but doesn't yet call the LLM to *decide what to do next*. Right now, steps must be submitted externally.

**What's needed:**
- [ ] **LLM Planning Loop**: Wire the `AutonomousAgentLoop.executeGoal()` method to call the configured LLM provider, pass the goal + current state, and receive tool-call decisions
- [ ] **Perception → Action Cycle**: Browser agent perceives page state (accessibility tree or screenshot) → sends to LLM → LLM decides next action → agent executes → loops
- [ ] **Computer agent planning**: Similar loop for shell commands — LLM sees system state, decides what command to run
- [ ] **Conversation memory**: The loop needs a message history buffer so the LLM can reason over past steps
- [ ] Wire `AutonomousBrowserAgent.executeObjective()` to use the LLM delegate from `DashboardService.getLlmDelegate()`
- [ ] Wire `AutonomousComputerAgent.executeObjective()` similarly

**Files to modify:**
- `src/core/runtime/autonomous-agent-loop.ts` — Add `executeGoal()` with LLM loop
- `src/core/runtime/autonomous-browser-agent.ts` — Wire `perceive()` → LLM → `act()`
- `src/core/runtime/autonomous-computer-agent.ts` — Wire LLM reasoning

**Estimated effort:** 2-3 sessions

