### Priority 3: Watch Me — Behavioral Replay & Training

> [!NOTE]
> The "Watch Me" tab has a **working UI** with session selection, prompt input, live timeline, and screenshot polling. It pipes into `AgenticChatExecutor` via WebSocket. What's missing is the recording/replay/training layer.

**What's needed:**
- [ ] **Recording**: Capture autonomous run sequences to disk as JSON replay files (goal + steps + tool calls + results)
- [ ] **Replay**: Load and replay a recorded session in the Watch Me timeline (read-only)
- [ ] **Training Model Generation**: Export recorded sequences as fine-tuning datasets (input: state → output: tool call)
- [ ] Wire the existing `replay.ts` module (which has comparison/normalization utilities) into the Watch Me controller

**Files to modify:**
- `src/core/runtime/replay.ts` — Add recording/export functions
- `tab-watch.js` — Add record/replay UI controls
- New: `src/core/runtime/replay-recorder.ts` — Session recording service

**Estimated effort:** 1-2 sessions

